Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,[Eyecatch]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 984 "Kid vs. \NKomei: The Targeted Lips (Part Two)"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[OP]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,MOENA,0000,0000,0000,,[ED]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.32,0:00:05.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The world's largest conch pearl, Fairy Lip.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.50,0:00:09.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In order to face off against \NKid, whose target is the jewel,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.90,0:00:15.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hattori and I came to Suzuki \NJirokichi's Suzuki Museum.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.96,0:00:19.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Also there to take on Kid was \NInspector Morofushi Takaaki
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.27,0:00:22.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,of the Nagano Prefectural Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.81,0:00:25.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But despite that,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.17,0:00:29.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kid was able to steal the pearl \Nfrozen inside a block of ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.22,0:00:34.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Find the question that solves the mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.91,0:00:36.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Apply miraculous detective skills \Nto the secrets of the heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.95,0:00:38.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Both Kid and Heiji are targeting lips!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.97,0:00:41.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Where will the missing jewel \Nand their love end up?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.19,0:00:42.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.80,0:00:44.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.63,0:00:47.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.00,0:02:33.00,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(397,1)}Kid vs. Komei: The Targeted Lips \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.50,0:02:31.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"Kid vs. Komei: The Targeted Lips, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.38,0:02:35.75,StolenNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,The fairy's lips are mine \NKaito Kid
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.75,0:02:36.51,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.65,0:02:39.88,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,I knew the ice wasn't enough to keep it safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.88,0:02:44.26,DCMain,HIROKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,But what are all these rings?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.26,0:02:44.26,StolenNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,The fairy's lips are mine \NKaito Kid
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.57,0:02:47.14,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,It's a floral ice performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.14,0:02:48.06,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.34,0:02:50.94,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,It's an art that involves drilling \Nholes with an electric drill
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.26,0:02:53.77,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,and using food coloring to stain the ice
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.77,0:02:58.94,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,to make it appear as though there \Nare real flowers inside the ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.55,0:03:03.20,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,Kid simply used that method to \Ncreate rings instead of flowers,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.73,0:03:07.70,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,with unimaginable speed, \Nin order to throw us off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.92,0:03:11.64,DCMain,JIROKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,But this room was pitch black.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.64,0:03:12.96,DCMain,JIROKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,How did he do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.16,0:03:15.84,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You guys inside didn't see anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.11,0:03:17.05,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Nah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.05,0:03:19.86,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Like the old man said, it was pitch black.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.86,0:03:20.63,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.63,0:03:23.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he went under the sheet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.59,0:03:27.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The clear sheet over the ice \Nwas stained black by the ink.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.05,0:03:32.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He could've drilled the holes by \Nslipping inside and turning on a light.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.43,0:03:36.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There are tools next to the \Nice, so that must've been it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.17,0:03:38.13,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.13,0:03:40.13,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,That would allow him to \Nsecretly drill the holes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.13,0:03:41.24,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.24,0:03:44.37,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Since the light couldn't \Nget out, we didn't notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.62,0:03:46.58,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,I've had enough of this farce.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.58,0:03:47.37,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.71,0:03:50.12,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,You're the only ones who entered this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.12,0:03:54.12,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,I know one of you is Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.43,0:03:57.17,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to be stripped \Nand thoroughly searched.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.17,0:03:58.13,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.41,0:03:59.63,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.82,0:04:01.92,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Help, Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.41,0:04:07.81,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,He's going to strip me naked!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.93,0:04:10.56,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I-I wouldn't want you to be naked...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.81,0:04:11.90,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.90,0:04:15.28,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What about the sensor inside the ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.28,0:04:18.85,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,If someone exits through \Nthose doors with the ring,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.85,0:04:20.57,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,the sensor triggers an alarm, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.57,0:04:21.82,DCMain,JIROKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.25,0:04:27.45,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Then wait to search us until \Nafter the alarm has sounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.45,0:04:28.33,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Good thinking, Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.32,0:04:34.58,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,We're leaving the room, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.85,0:04:38.09,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,If the alarm goes off,\NI'm arresting both of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.35,0:04:40.22,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Fine by me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.39,0:04:52.34,DCMain,JIROKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.34,0:04:53.42,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.42,0:04:55.39,DCMain,JIROKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Then how did he...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.55,0:04:57.15,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,How did he get the ring outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.57,0:05:00.27,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Heiji, thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.27,0:05:01.65,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,G-Get off of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.42,0:05:04.07,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kazuha-chan's being so bold.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.65,0:05:09.22,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I-In any case, this means \Nneither of us are Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.22,0:05:10.59,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.59,0:05:13.50,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,This guy is too easy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.92,0:05:16.00,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,F-Fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.00,0:05:18.54,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,Time to finish this off.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.19,0:05:20.65,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.17,0:05:27.38,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Because of the commotion over Kid, I forgot \Nto get my phone from the glass box.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.38,0:05:28.89,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You're hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.31,0:05:30.99,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.66,0:05:34.51,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Is her phone over there somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.51,0:05:35.68,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.81,0:05:37.77,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,Is this it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.14,0:05:39.62,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.62,0:05:40.68,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.93,0:05:43.19,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,So cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.19,0:05:45.49,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It really is too cold in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.70,0:05:47.74,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,The AC is too cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.74,0:05:50.60,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, the ring's already been stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.60,0:05:52.47,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,We don't need the ice anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.47,0:05:54.26,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,Tell them to turn off the AC.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.26,0:05:55.00,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.54,0:05:58.50,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,We need to start collecting fingerprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.84,0:06:04.70,DCMain,JIROKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,But, Inspector, we still don't \Nknow how Kid stole the ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.70,0:06:07.84,DCMain,JIROKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Should we really melt the ice?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.84,0:06:09.64,DCMain,JIROKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Inspector Morofushi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.64,0:06:11.57,DCMain,JIROKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.17,0:06:16.77,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,No. Let's abandon the ice since \NKid managed to get around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.22,0:06:20.05,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,For now, we should search \Nevery inch of this room
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.05,0:06:24.27,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,to determine how he entered \Nand where he went.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.55,0:06:26.65,DCMain,JIROKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,If you say so...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.97,0:06:28.79,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,All right. It's perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.79,0:06:30.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Kazuha-neechan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.12,0:06:33.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you need to use the bathroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.51,0:06:36.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You've been keeping your knees together \Nand crouching this whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.03,0:06:40.92,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's right. I'm a \Nlittle cold from the AC.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.92,0:06:43.68,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you shouldn't ask girls that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.68,0:06:46.50,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to the \Nbathroom, I'll go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.50,0:06:49.34,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I want to wash this ink off my face.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.34,0:06:51.14,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.14,0:06:52.59,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, see you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.97,0:06:57.47,DCMain,TORIGOE,0000,0000,0000,,But now that the jewel has been stolen,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.64,0:07:01.06,Naeji,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Torigoe Naeji (45) \NGemstone Broker
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.89,0:07:00.86,DCMain,TORIGOE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm going to take what's mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.11,0:07:03.73,DCMain,TORIGOE,0000,0000,0000,,The substantial compensation I'm owed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.96,0:07:06.06,DCMain,JIROKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.81,0:07:14.20,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,Kansuke-kun, why are you calling so late?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.37,0:07:16.45,HQ,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Nagano Prefectural Police HQ
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.44,0:07:16.45,DCMain,KANSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Don't give me that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.45,0:07:22.68,DCMain,KANSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Komei, you said you'd call once you \Ncaught that Kaito whatever thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.68,0:07:25.28,DCMain,KANSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,It's way past when he said he'd come.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.28,0:07:26.92,DCMain,KANSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Why haven't you called?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.92,0:07:27.84,DCMain,YUI,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.46,0:07:31.08,DCMain,YUI,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's waiting at the station for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.30,0:07:33.47,DCItalic,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.89,0:07:39.14,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,The thief left a card saying "the \Njewel is mine" and vanished.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.14,0:07:41.80,DCMain,KANSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously? He beat you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.80,0:07:43.12,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.63,0:07:46.15,DCMain,KANSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,You don't seem very disappointed, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.71,0:07:53.41,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,"A commander neither delights in \Nvictory nor despairs in defeat."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.05,0:07:55.98,DCItalic,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,A commander does not become \Noverjoyed when he wins,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.98,0:07:59.42,DCItalic,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,nor does he become dejected when he loses.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.42,0:08:01.41,DCMain,KANSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,More sayings?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.02,0:08:04.94,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, this battle isn't over yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.96,0:08:08.73,DCMain,KANSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, what \Nabout that other thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.73,0:08:11.18,DCMain,KANSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,What about the package \Nreally addressed to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.18,0:08:14.05,DCItalic,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm planning on picking it up tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.51,0:08:17.13,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose it's already tomorrow \Nsince it's past midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.13,0:08:21.63,DCItalic,KANSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,But you don't remember \Nthe name of the officer
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.63,0:08:23.46,DCItalic,KANSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,who left the envelope in your locker, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.46,0:08:26.83,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,No, but despite being rather blurry,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.83,0:08:30.52,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,the name written on the \Nnote stuck to the envelope
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.52,0:08:33.32,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,could be read as my mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.58,0:08:36.45,DCMain,KANSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,But do you know anyone in Tokyo?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.45,0:08:40.33,DCMain,YUI,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you have a younger brother at the MPD?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.54,0:08:41.41,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.41,0:08:46.33,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps my brother knows the \Nofficer who had the package.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.55,0:08:50.29,DCMain,KANSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you have your \Nbrother check it out, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.29,0:08:52.75,DCItalic,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,He left the force a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.75,0:08:57.07,DCItalic,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't heard anything from him \Nsince he said he found another job.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.23,0:09:03.46,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea where he \Nis or what he's doing now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.84,0:09:09.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, since Kid already came and \Nleft, let's take a taxi home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.15,0:09:10.90,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.90,0:09:12.90,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Taking a taxi would be a waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.32,0:09:16.07,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But there's still about four hours \Nbefore the trains start running.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.21,0:09:20.89,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's take a nap in \Nthe museum somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.89,0:09:22.13,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.13,0:09:25.33,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go ask Jirokichi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.33,0:09:27.46,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.88,0:09:31.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Despite everything, those two sure are close.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.92,0:09:32.84,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.84,0:09:36.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, Heiji-niichan's sticking \Nby her so she doesn't escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.80,0:09:38.22,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Escape?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.47,0:09:42.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That Kazuha-neechan is actually Kaito Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.35,0:09:45.52,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.52,0:09:46.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.89,0:09:48.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.47,0:09:52.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She's been bending her knees this whole time,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.10,0:09:56.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and the real Kazuha-neechan\Nrefers to herself as "atashi,"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.03,0:09:58.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but that one calls herself "uchi."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.50,0:10:01.72,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.72,0:10:04.75,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then why is he still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.46,0:10:09.17,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's only one possible reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.61,0:10:15.51,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,It's so soft.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.84,0:10:19.51,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you could sleep soundly on this couch.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.82,0:10:20.88,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.88,0:10:23.16,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's go get Ran-chan and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.16,0:10:25.51,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't like AC units.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.51,0:10:27.52,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt I can sleep without a fan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.05,0:10:31.74,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,If you can't sleep, I'll sleep next to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.74,0:10:33.82,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.82,0:10:35.76,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.76,0:10:37.74,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,That would make it harder to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.94,0:11:00.94,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Enough already.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.17,0:11:05.06,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Everything you've been saying is ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.40,0:11:06.18,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.70,0:11:08.64,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I'll have to cover \Nthat ridiculous mouth...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.18,0:11:12.56,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,in order to keep you quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.85,0:11:14.06,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.45,0:11:19.44,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.75,0:11:20.66,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.13,0:11:22.19,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.84,0:11:26.05,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.44,0:11:34.25,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I'll have to cover \Nthat ridiculous mouth...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.75,0:11:39.01,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,in order to keep you quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.60,0:11:40.51,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.00,0:11:42.01,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.51,0:11:43.51,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.41,0:11:45.26,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.69,0:11:46.76,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.15,0:11:49.93,DCItalic,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.88,0:11:53.80,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.36,0:11:59.01,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What's all the noise for?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.60,0:12:01.42,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You surprised us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.42,0:12:06.49,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,W-We came in a hurry since we were so sleepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.70,0:12:08.36,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That was close.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.36,0:12:13.75,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe Hattori hasn't \Nnoticed that's Kid in disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.19,0:12:16.98,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, he did \Nbecome a crap detective
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.98,0:12:20.88,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,when Kazuha-chan got involved at \NEbisubashi Bridge in Osaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.00,0:12:24.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, this room is pretty big.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.22,0:12:27.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There's even a soft couch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.19,0:12:31.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't mind sleeping in here until noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.77,0:12:34.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I am the Sleeping Kogoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.06,0:12:37.06,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.85,0:12:58.21,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,It's been about four hours since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.54,0:12:59.94,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,Should be ready soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.72,0:13:07.49,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's melted quite a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.49,0:13:10.26,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried since it was \Naround three meters tall,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.52,0:13:12.89,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,but it has been hot lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.50,0:13:15.53,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to go make my report.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.49,0:13:17.60,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.05,0:13:22.11,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,I seem to have dropped a \Ncontact inside the glass box.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.66,0:13:24.70,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Could I go in and get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.70,0:13:26.01,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.01,0:13:27.22,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.22,0:13:30.17,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,The floor is wet from the \Nmelted ice, so be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.17,0:13:31.37,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.94,0:13:35.37,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Where was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.78,0:13:38.33,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.38,0:13:43.46,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.72,0:13:50.22,DCItalic,KID,0000,0000,0000,,The world's largest pearl is mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.15,0:13:55.27,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,"One hundred saw-wings are \Nno match for one raptor."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.47,0:13:56.64,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.14,0:13:59.15,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,Saw-wings refers to sparrows,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.43,0:14:01.77,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,and the raptor refers to the hawk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.15,0:14:04.75,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, even if a \Nhundred swallows come together,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.75,0:14:07.74,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,they cannot defeat a single hawk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.15,0:14:09.99,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,It seems you attempted to throw us off
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.15,0:14:13.60,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,by making countless rings appear in the ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.08,0:14:16.82,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,and drilled a large hole through the middle
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.16,0:14:21.86,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,to make us believe you'd \Nstolen the real ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.56,0:14:24.62,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,But you can't fool my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.33,0:14:31.93,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,One hundred fake rings can't compare \Nto the beauty of a true conch pearl.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.20,0:14:33.52,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.52,0:14:36.81,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,You knew, so you were \Nwaiting to see what I'd do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.09,0:14:38.04,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.04,0:14:41.90,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd try to catch you in the act.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.49,0:14:47.53,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,Then naturally, you knew \Nthis was my disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.80,0:14:48.76,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.76,0:14:52.20,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,Your first person pronoun switched \Nfrom "atashi" to "uchi,"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.20,0:14:55.43,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,and you were crouching to \Nmake yourself appear shorter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.01,0:14:58.88,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,The rest of you noticed as well, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.88,0:14:59.52,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.52,0:15:00.17,DCMain,JIROKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.17,0:15:00.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Ofâ€”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.65,0:15:01.67,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.88,0:15:03.75,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.75,0:15:06.21,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,But if you knew all that,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.48,0:15:09.47,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,you should've retrieved the real ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.38,0:15:16.64,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It's all white this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.64,0:15:19.22,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't panic. It's just a smoke screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.22,0:15:21.86,DCMain,JIROKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,We can vent all the smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.86,0:15:25.65,DCMain,JIROKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Since the entrance is sealed, he'll \Nbe caught like a rat in a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.26,0:15:29.24,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,The smoke is clearing, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.90,0:15:31.59,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,What's that hole?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.59,0:15:32.66,DCMain,JIROKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,When did that get there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.93,0:15:35.62,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,So that's his escape route.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.62,0:15:37.46,DCMain,JIROKICHI,0000,0000,0000,,You knew?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.46,0:15:40.85,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but I chose to ignore it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.85,0:15:46.17,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,I heard Kaito Kid returns the jewel to \Nits owner if it's not the one he wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.33,0:15:50.86,DCMain,TORIGOE,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, then it'll be returned to me later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.86,0:15:55.74,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,If you're the real owner of the jewel.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.74,0:15:56.88,DCMain,TORIGOE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.88,0:15:58.96,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you say the pearl was \Nfound inside a giant oyster
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.96,0:16:04.18,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,sleeping at the bottom of \NMie Prefecture's Ago Bay,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.18,0:16:08.32,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,and that you were drawn to the \Npearl's unique orient effect?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.63,0:16:10.13,DCMain,TORIGOE,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.13,0:16:15.65,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,But real conch pearls are only \Nharvested from pink conches
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.19,0:16:17.67,Sea,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,420)}Caribbean Sea
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.19,0:16:17.70,Gulf,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,420)}Gulf of Mexico
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.65,0:16:17.76,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,in the Gulf of Mexico or the Caribbean Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.76,0:16:21.20,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,And it's not the rainbow "orient \Neffect" that defines conch pearls,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.38,0:16:25.79,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,it's their beautiful "flame \Npattern" wavy lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.55,0:16:27.68,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.50,0:16:31.88,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,you're not the real owner of that jewel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.23,0:16:36.10,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It belongs to that girl who said her \Ngrandfather received it as a gift
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.88,0:16:36.34,Moena,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Yamamoto Moena (21) \NOffice Worker
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.10,0:16:38.76,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}from a wealthy Caribbean man.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.40,0:16:42.78,DCMain,NAKAMORI,0000,0000,0000,,You can tell us all about it later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.78,0:16:45.02,DCMain,TORIGOE,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, um, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.52,0:16:50.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You noticed that gemstone \Nbroker was suspicious, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.49,0:16:54.52,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, at least I noticed this \None was fake right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.52,0:16:57.36,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, "this one?"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.12,0:17:03.29,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Heiji, are you saying you didn't \Nnotice Kid was disguised as me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.74,0:17:04.62,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.62,0:17:07.48,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I noticed right away, but I was \Nwaiting to see what he'd do!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.48,0:17:08.92,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.16,0:17:10.84,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,What was different?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.10,0:17:13.44,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I-It was...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.61,0:17:15.84,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.33,0:17:18.09,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The seaweed!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.09,0:17:21.92,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,The fake Kazuha didn't have \Nany seaweed in her teeth!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.33,0:17:25.60,DCMain,KAZUHA,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-chan, I knew it was seaweed!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.41,0:17:30.54,DCMain,HEIJI,0000,0000,0000,,A-Anyway, I wonder where that thief went.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.54,0:17:35.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's likely he sped things up because \Nhe was suspicious of the jewel's owner,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.66,0:17:37.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so he's probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.09,0:17:40.12,DCMain,MOENA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Grandma.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.48,0:17:46.12,DCMain,MOENA,0000,0000,0000,,I wish you could've taken the jewel you \Ngot from grandpa to heaven with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.47,0:17:48.21,DCMain,MOENA,0000,0000,0000,,But I couldn't get it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.79,0:17:51.52,DCMain,MOENA,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I'd asked you more \Nabout that pink pearl
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.52,0:17:54.27,DCMain,MOENA,0000,0000,0000,,while you were alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.88,0:17:57.56,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly 50 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.56,0:18:01.31,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,while a wealthy Caribbean man was \Ntraveling around the world by boat,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.31,0:18:06.14,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,his pregnant wife suddenly went into labor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.72,0:18:09.92,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,By chance, your grandfather who was a surgeon
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.92,0:18:12.40,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,happened to be on that same \Nboat on his honeymoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.69,0:18:14.49,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,Though it wasn't his specialty,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.49,0:18:18.15,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,he used his medical knowledge \Nto help with the birth
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.15,0:18:23.25,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,And it was with gratitude \Nthat the Caribbean man
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.25,0:18:25.54,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,gave this Fairy Lip to your grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.30,0:18:28.16,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,Yamamoto Moena-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.31,0:18:30.54,DCMain,MOENA,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.46,0:18:32.89,DCMain,MOENA,0000,0000,0000,,Kaito Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.94,0:18:40.08,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,The details of the event were written \Non the son's blog in Spanish.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.08,0:18:45.31,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,That broker probably plotted to \Nsteal your jewel after reading it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.72,0:18:51.81,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, this jewel doesn't \Nseem to have been the one I wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.19,0:18:57.52,DCMain,KID,0000,0000,0000,,May I add a touch of color to your \Ngrandmother's cruise through the afterlife?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.64,0:19:05.66,DCMain,MOENA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.32,0:19:11.44,DCMain,MOENA,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.68,0:20:38.29,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What? A package was found \Nin Date-san's locker?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.76,0:20:39.78,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.78,0:20:43.57,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,To be precise, inside the \Npackage sent to Date-san
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.57,0:20:48.68,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,was an envelope with a note asking that \Nit be sent to an inspector in Nagano.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.42,0:20:54.14,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,We'd left there it since he passed away \Nin a traffic accident one year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.57,0:20:58.19,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,The writing on the note had bled, \Nso it was pretty hard to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.43,0:21:03.55,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Was the sender's name blurry, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.55,0:21:05.32,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,There wasn't one written.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.78,0:21:08.12,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,Look, there's only a circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.41,0:21:12.14,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe it was left in \Nhis locker for a whole year.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.14,0:21:14.11,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.11,0:21:18.59,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,It was stuffed full of things he \Nshould've thrown out like photos
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.59,0:21:20.13,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,and things from his police academy days.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.28,0:21:21.27,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.27,0:21:25.38,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Sato-san, you don't have good \Nmemories of the police academy?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.35,0:21:28.24,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.24,0:21:33.19,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,Because Date-san and his \Nclass were so unruly,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.19,0:21:38.19,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,they were unbelievably \Nstrict on my class only.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.19,0:21:41.57,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,Matsuda-kun was in that class, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.17,0:21:46.01,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, weren't Date-san \Nand Matsuda-san in the same class?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.01,0:21:48.49,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you only refer to \NMatsuda-san as Matsuda-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.82,0:21:54.25,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,Because unlike Date-san, I became a \Npolice officer before Matsuda-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.78,0:21:55.87,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.76,0:21:57.94,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.00,0:22:01.75,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,This is the envelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.00,0:22:04.60,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure it's addressed to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.60,0:22:05.38,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.81,0:22:07.23,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,It is surely addressed to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.23,0:22:09.61,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's check its contents.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.61,0:22:10.26,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.08,0:22:14.00,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,This...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.37,0:22:16.77,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,It's a phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.30,0:22:19.27,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,There's a hole through the middle, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.64,0:22:21.04,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,That's definitely a hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.04,0:22:22.92,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What's it from?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.72,0:22:26.53,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,There's a black stain around \Nthe inside of the hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.40,0:22:31.61,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,and on the back is a uniquely written \NH made to look like a scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.30,0:22:37.29,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,"With life comes death, and life is short."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.53,0:22:38.47,DCMain,SATO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.47,0:22:40.65,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,"People cannot avoid death."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.65,0:22:43.58,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,"Our short lives are destined to end."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.58,0:22:46.67,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,It's what a Chinese general once said.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.53,0:22:49.94,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,This phone belonged to my younger brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.40,0:22:54.68,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,He said he quit the force,\Nbut if this was delivered here,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.26,0:22:57.52,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,then he was probably working \Nfor the Public Security Agency
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.52,0:23:00.43,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,and lost his life while working undercover.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.91,0:23:04.46,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,After all, this is probably a bullet hole, \Nand this black stain is probably blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.07,0:23:07.38,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.69,0:23:09.71,Morofushi,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Morofushi Takaaki-sama
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.71,0:23:10.70,Morofushi,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Bro, \Nstarting today, \NI'm a cop too!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.56,0:23:12.63,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,Hiromitsu...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.66,0:23:15.28,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Metropolitan Police Department
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.39,0:23:18.22,DCMain,KOMEI,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.22,0:23:20.13,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all. Thank you for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.41,0:23:29.92,DCItalic,HIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Bro!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.71,0:23:33.43,DCItalic,HIRO,0000,0000,0000,,I made a friend in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.77,0:23:36.16,DCItalic,HIRO,0000,0000,0000,,His nickname is Zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.63,0:23:42.22,DCItalic,HIRO,0000,0000,0000,,Pretty cool, right?
